solution:
Since $BC = 8$ and $M$ is the midpoint of $BC$, $BM = CM = 4$.  But $AM = 4$, so $M$ is the circumcenter of triangle $ABC$.  Furthermore, $BC$ is a diameter of the circle, so $\angle BAC = 90^\circ$.

[asy]

unitsize(2 cm);

pair A, B, C, M;

A = dir(110);

B = (-1,0);

C = (1,0);

M = (0,0);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);

