label("$A$", A, dir(90));

label("$B$", B, SW);

label("$C$", C, SE);

dot("$M$", M, S);

[/asy]

Then by Pythagoras on right triangle $ABC$, $AC = \sqrt{BC^2 - AB^2} = \sqrt{8^2 - 5^2} = \sqrt{64 - 25} = \boxed{\sqrt{39}}$.

We draw right triangle $GAC$ within the cube below:

